- The integer matrix parameter `mat` must not be null.
- The integer result is the number of special positions in the integer matrix `mat`.
- A position `(i, j)` is considered special if `mat[i][j]` is equal to 1 and all other elements in row `i` and column `j` are equal to 0.
- Rows and columns are 0-indexed.
- The integer result is greater than or equal to 0.